\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Roasted Smoky Cauliflower with Limey Yogurt\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 4 to 6 servings\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\ql\qnatural

\fs36 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 medium cauliflower heads (use different colors if you can find them), stripped of leaves and main stalk chopped off\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/3 cup extra-virgin olive oil, plus a splash\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon ground coriander\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon dried {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mango/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mango}} powder ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/amchoor/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 amchoor}}, found at Indian stores, optional)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon ground cumin\
{\listtext	\'95	}Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup Greek yogurt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lime/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lime}}, zested, plus a squeeze of juice\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment.\
Break up the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cauliflower/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cauliflower}} into evenly sized florets about 1-inch long. You can use a knife to divide the large florets if they don't break easily.\
In a large bowl, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 whisk}} together 1/3 cup oil, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/coriander/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 coriander}}, mango powder, if using, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cumin/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cumin}}, salt and pepper, to taste. Add the florets and, using your hands, gently toss to coat.\
Pour the prepared baking sheet and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/roast/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 roast}} until tender and slightly browned, 30 to 40 minutes, tossing halfway through.\
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/yogurt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 yogurt}} with the lime {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/zest/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 zest}}, a splash of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/olive-oil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 extra-virgin olive oil}}, salt, pepper, and a squeeze of lime (as much as you like).\
Serve the cauliflower with a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/dollop/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 dollop}} of yogurt on the side, and enjoy a whole new way to eat cauliflower!\
